                 \n    \n\n\u003cp\u003eYou really can\u0026#39;t go wrong by investing in a smart tag. And for Samsung device owners, the SmartTag 2 is going to be the one. Not only do you get something compact, but it\u0026#39;s also quite durable thanks to its fantastic design and also has an IP67 rating as well.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eBut what\u0026#39;s really important here is its ability to track things. While you can slip this into a bag or purse, you can also attach it to products using its built-in key ring. Using Samsung\u0026#39;s SmartThings app, you\u0026#39;ll be able to easily track the smart tags whereabouts. \u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003ePlus you\u0026#39;ll get alerts if you ever leave something behind, and with \u003ca href=\"http://www.androidpolice.com/samsung-smarttag-2-uwb/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eUWB\u003c/a\u003e, you\u0026#39;ll get accurate directions to the location of a lost item that has the smart tag attached. And as far as battery life goes, it\u0026#39;s absolutely fantastic, with the ability to last up to 700 days if needed.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eThe good news here is that there\u0026#39;s no charging required. If you ever have a smart tag that\u0026#39;s low on power, you can just pop into a store, \u003ca href=\"http://www.androidpolice.com/samsung-smarttag-2-battery-replaceable/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ebuy a common button battery and easily replace it\u003c/a\u003e. Perhaps the only drawback of this product is that it is only compatible with Samsung Galaxy devices. \u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eSo if you\u0026#39;ve been looking to keep better track of your things, then the Samsung SmartTag 2 is going to be the one to get. Just be sure to act quickly as this deal won\u0026#39;t be around for too long. And if you aren\u0026#39;t sure, be sure to check out our other \u003ca href=\"http://www.androidpolice.com/best-smart-tags/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003esmart tag recommendations\u003c/a\u003e. \u003c/p\u003